<li id="cite_note-33"><b><a href="#cite_ref-33" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal" class=""><i><a href="http://www.blurtit.com/q497068.html" class="external text" title="http://www.blurtit.com/q497068.html" rel="nofollow">Are polar bears left-handed or right-handed?</a></i>, September 2006<span class="printonly">, <a href="http://www.blurtit.com/q497068.html" class="external free" title="http://www.blurtit.com/q497068.html" rel="nofollow">http://www.blurtit.com/q497068.html</a></span><span class="reference-accessdate">, retrieved on 2007-11-25</span></cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Are+polar+bears+left-handed+or+right-handed%3F&amp;rft.date=September+2006&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.blurtit.com%2Fq497068.html&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Polar_bear"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span>.</li>
<li id="cite_note-34"><b><a href="#cite_ref-34" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal" class=""><i><a href="http://www.polarbearsinternational.org/bear-facts/myths-and-misconceptions/" class="external text" title="http://www.polarbearsinternational.org/bear-facts/myths-and-misconceptions/" rel="nofollow">Bear Facts: Myths and Misconceptions</a></i>, 2007<span class="printonly">, <a href="http://www.polarbearsinternational.org/bear-facts/myths-and-misconceptions/" class="external free" title="http://www.polarbearsinternational.org/bear-facts/myths-and-misconceptions/" rel="nofollow">http://www.polarbearsinternational.org/bear-facts/myths-and-misconceptions/</a></span><span class="reference-accessdate">, retrieved on 2007-11-25</span></cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Bear+Facts%3A+Myths+and+Misconceptions&amp;rft.date=2007&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.polarbearsinternational.org%2Fbear-facts%2Fmyths-and-misconceptions%2F&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Polar_bear"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span>.</li>
<li id="cite_note-35"><b><a href="#cite_ref-35" title="">^</a></b> Researchers studying polar bears have failed to find any evidence of left-handedness in all bears and one study of injury patterns in polar bear forelimbs found injuries to the right forelimb to be more frequent than those to the left, suggesting, perhaps, right-handedness. <cite style="font-style:normal" class=""><i><a href="http://www.polarbearsinternational.org/pbhc/fractures.htm" class="external text" title="http://www.polarbearsinternational.org/pbhc/fractures.htm" rel="nofollow">Fractures of the Radius and Ulna secondary to possible Vitamin 'D' deficiency in Captive Polar Bears (Ursus maritimus<i>)</i></a></i><span class="printonly">, <a href="http://www.polarbearsinternational.org/pbhc/fractures.htm" class="external free" title="http://www.polarbearsinternational.org/pbhc/fractures.htm" rel="nofollow">http://www.polarbearsinternational.org/pbhc/fractures.htm</a></span><span class="reference-accessdate">, retrieved on 2007-11-25</span></cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Fractures+of+the+Radius+and+Ulna+secondary+to+possible+Vitamin+%27D%27+deficiency+in+Captive+Polar+Bears+%28%27%27Ursus+maritimus%27%27%29&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.polarbearsinternational.org%2Fpbhc%2Ffractures.htm&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Polar_bear"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span>.</li>
<li id="cite_note-stirling1988-36">^ <a href="#cite_ref-stirling1988_36-0" title=""><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-stirling1988_36-1" title=""><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-stirling1988_36-2" title=""><sup><i><b>c</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-stirling1988_36-3" title=""><sup><i><b>d</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-stirling1988_36-4" title=""><sup><i><b>e</b></i></sup></a> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="" id="CITEREFStirling1988"><a href="/wiki/Ian_Stirling" title="Ian Stirling">Stirling, Ian</a> (1988), <i>Polar Bears</i>, Ann Arbor: University of Michigan Press, <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0472101005" class="internal">ISBN 0-472-10100-5</a></cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Polar+Bears&amp;rft.aulast=Stirling&amp;rft.aufirst=Ian&amp;rft.au=Stirling%2C+Ian&amp;rft.date=1988&amp;rft.place=Ann+Arbor&amp;rft.pub=University+of+Michigan+Press&amp;rft.isbn=0-472-10100-5&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Polar_bear"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li id="cite_note-37"><b><a href="#cite_ref-37" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="book" id="CITEREFUspenskii1977">Uspenskii, S. M. (1977). <i>The Polar Bear</i>. Moscow: Nauka.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=The+Polar+Bear&amp;rft.aulast=Uspenskii&amp;rft.aufirst=S.+M.&amp;rft.au=Uspenskii%2C+S.+M.&amp;rft.date=1977&amp;rft.place=Moscow&amp;rft.pub=Nauka&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Polar_bear"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li id="cite_note-38"><b><a href="#cite_ref-38" title="">^</a></b> Kolenosky G. B. 1987. Polar bear. pp. 475–485 in Wild furbearer management and conservation in North America (M. Novak, J. A. Baker, M. E. Obbard, and B. Malloch, eds.). Ontario Fur Trappers Association, North Bay, Ontario, Canada.</li>
<li id="cite_note-39"><b><a href="#cite_ref-39" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="" id="CITEREFKoon1998">Koon, Daniel W. (1998), "<a href="http://www.opticsinfobase.org/abstract.cfm?URI=ao-37-15-3198" class="external text" title="http://www.opticsinfobase.org/abstract.cfm?URI=ao-37-15-3198" rel="nofollow">Is Polar Bear Hair Fiber Optic?</a>", <i>Applied Optics</i> (<a href="/wiki/Optical_Society_of_America" title="Optical Society of America">Optical Society of America</a>) <b>37</b> (15): 3198–3200, <a href="/wiki/Digital_object_identifier" title="Digital object identifier">doi</a>:<span class="neverexpand"><a href="http://dx.doi.org/10.1364%2FAO.37.003198" class="external text" title="http://dx.doi.org/10.1364%2FAO.37.003198" rel="nofollow">10.1364/AO.37.003198</a></span><span class="printonly">, <a href="http://www.opticsinfobase.org/abstract.cfm?URI=ao-37-15-3198" class="external free" title="http://www.opticsinfobase.org/abstract.cfm?URI=ao-37-15-3198" rel="nofollow">http://www.opticsinfobase.org/abstract.cfm?URI=ao-37-15-3198</a></span></cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.atitle=Is+Polar+Bear+Hair+Fiber+Optic%3F&amp;rft.jtitle=Applied+Optics&amp;rft.aulast=Koon&amp;rft.aufirst=Daniel+W.&amp;rft.au=Koon%2C+Daniel+W.&amp;rft.date=1998&amp;rft.volume=37&amp;rft.issue=15&amp;rft.pages=3198%E2%80%933200&amp;rft.pub=%5B%5BOptical+Society+of+America%5D%5D&amp;rft_id=info:doi/10.1364%2FAO.37.003198&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.opticsinfobase.org%2Fabstract.cfm%3FURI%3Dao-37-15-3198&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Polar_bear"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span>.</li>
<li id="cite_note-40"><b><a href="#cite_ref-40" title="">^</a></b> In unusually warm conditions, the hollow tubes provide an excellent home for algae. While the algae is harmless to the bears, it is often a worry to the zoos housing them, and affected animals are sometimes washed in a salt solution, or mild <a href="/wiki/Hydrogen_peroxide" title="Hydrogen peroxide">peroxide bleach</a> to make the fur white again.</li>
