<li id="cite_note-original-73">^ <a href="#cite_ref-original_73-0" title=""><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-original_73-1" title=""><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-original_73-2" title=""><sup><i><b>c</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-original_73-3" title=""><sup><i><b>d</b></i></sup></a> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="book" id="CITEREFStirling1988">Stirling, Ian (1988). "The Original Polar Bear Watchers". <i>Polar Bears</i>. Ann Arbor: University of Michigan Press. <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0472101005" class="internal">ISBN 0-472-10100-5</a>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft.btitle=The+Original+Polar+Bear+Watchers&amp;rft.atitle=Polar+Bears&amp;rft.aulast=Stirling&amp;rft.aufirst=Ian&amp;rft.au=Stirling%2C+Ian&amp;rft.date=1988&amp;rft.place=Ann+Arbor&amp;rft.pub=University+of+Michigan+Press&amp;rft.isbn=0-472-10100-5&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Polar_bear"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li id="cite_note-lw6-9-74">^ <a href="#cite_ref-lw6-9_74-0" title=""><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-lw6-9_74-1" title=""><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a> Lockwood, pp 6-9</li>
<li id="cite_note-Uspensky-75">^ <a href="#cite_ref-Uspensky_75-0" title=""><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Uspensky_75-1" title=""><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Uspensky_75-2" title=""><sup><i><b>c</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Uspensky_75-3" title=""><sup><i><b>d</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Uspensky_75-4" title=""><sup><i><b>e</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Uspensky_75-5" title=""><sup><i><b>f</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Uspensky_75-6" title=""><sup><i><b>g</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Uspensky_75-7" title=""><sup><i><b>h</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Uspensky_75-8" title=""><sup><i><b>i</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Uspensky_75-9" title=""><sup><i><b>j</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Uspensky_75-10" title=""><sup><i><b>k</b></i></sup></a> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="book" id="CITEREFUspensky1977">Uspensky, Savva Mikhailovich (1977). <i>Белый Медведь (tr: Belyi Medved') - (in Russian)</i>. Moscow: Nauka.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=%D0%91%D0%B5%D0%BB%D1%8B%D0%B9+%D0%9C%D0%B5%D0%B4%D0%B2%D0%B5%D0%B4%D1%8C+%28tr%3A+Belyi+Medved%27%29+-+%28in+Russian%29&amp;rft.aulast=Uspensky&amp;rft.aufirst=Savva+Mikhailovich&amp;rft.au=Uspensky%2C+Savva+Mikhailovich&amp;rft.date=1977&amp;rft.place=Moscow&amp;rft.pub=Nauka&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Polar_bear"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li id="cite_note-76"><b><a href="#cite_ref-76" title="">^</a></b> As a carnivore which feeds largely upon <a href="/wiki/Fish" title="Fish">fish</a>-eating carnivores, the polar bear ingests large amounts of <a href="/wiki/Retinol" title="Retinol">vitamin A</a>, which is stored in their <a href="/wiki/Liver" title="Liver">livers</a>. The resulting high concentrations cause <a href="/wiki/Hypervitaminosis_A" title="Hypervitaminosis A">Hypervitaminosis A</a>,<cite style="font-style:normal" class="" id="CITEREFRodahlMoore1943">Rodahl, K.; Moore, T. (July 1943), "<a href="http://www.pubmedcentral.nih.gov/picrender.fcgi?artid=1257872&amp;blobtype=pdf" class="external text" title="http://www.pubmedcentral.nih.gov/picrender.fcgi?artid=1257872&amp;blobtype=pdf" rel="nofollow">The vitamin A content and toxicity of bear and seal liver</a>", <i>The Biochemical Journal</i> (London: Portland Press) <b>37</b> (2): 166–168, <a href="/wiki/International_Standard_Serial_Number" title="International Standard Serial Number">ISSN</a> <a href="http://worldcat.org/issn/0264-6021" class="external text" title="http://worldcat.org/issn/0264-6021" rel="nofollow">0264-6021</a><span class="printonly">, <a href="http://www.pubmedcentral.nih.gov/picrender.fcgi?artid=1257872&amp;blobtype=pdf" class="external free" title="http://www.pubmedcentral.nih.gov/picrender.fcgi?artid=1257872&amp;blobtype=pdf" rel="nofollow">http://www.pubmedcentral.nih.gov/picrender.fcgi?artid=1257872&amp;blobtype=pdf</a></span><span class="reference-accessdate">, retrieved on 2007-11-11</span></cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.atitle=The+vitamin+A+content+and+toxicity+of+bear+and+seal+liver&amp;rft.jtitle=The+Biochemical+Journal&amp;rft.aulast=Rodahl&amp;rft.aufirst=K.&amp;rft.au=Rodahl%2C+K.&amp;rft.au=Moore%2C+T.&amp;rft.date=July+1943&amp;rft.volume=37&amp;rft.issue=2&amp;rft.pages=166%E2%80%93168&amp;rft.place=London&amp;rft.pub=Portland+Press&amp;rft.issn=0264-6021&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.pubmedcentral.nih.gov%2Fpicrender.fcgi%3Fartid%3D1257872%26blobtype%3Dpdf&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Polar_bear"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span>.</li>
<li id="cite_note-lw31-36-77">^ <a href="#cite_ref-lw31-36_77-0" title=""><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-lw31-36_77-1" title=""><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a> Lockwood, pp. 31-36</li>
<li id="cite_note-nwt-78"><b><a href="#cite_ref-nwt_78-0" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="web"><a href="http://wildlife.enr.gov.nt.ca/NWTWildlife/bears/PolarBear/management.htm" class="external text" title="http://wildlife.enr.gov.nt.ca/NWTWildlife/bears/PolarBear/management.htm" rel="nofollow">"Polar Bear Management"</a>. Government of the Northwest Territories<span class="printonly">. <a href="http://wildlife.enr.gov.nt.ca/NWTWildlife/bears/PolarBear/management.htm" class="external free" title="http://wildlife.enr.gov.nt.ca/NWTWildlife/bears/PolarBear/management.htm" rel="nofollow">http://wildlife.enr.gov.nt.ca/NWTWildlife/bears/PolarBear/management.htm</a></span><span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved on 2008-03-14</span>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft.btitle=Polar+Bear+Management&amp;rft.atitle=&amp;rft.pub=Government+of+the+Northwest+Territories&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwildlife.enr.gov.nt.ca%2FNWTWildlife%2Fbears%2FPolarBear%2Fmanagement.htm&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Polar_bear"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li id="cite_note-bruemmer93-111-79">^ <a href="#cite_ref-bruemmer93-111_79-0" title=""><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-bruemmer93-111_79-1" title=""><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a> Bruemmer, pp. 93-111</li>
<li id="cite_note-PBSG2-80"><b><a href="#cite_ref-PBSG2_80-0" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal">(February 1970) "<a href="http://pbsg.npolar.no/Meetings/PressReleases/02-Morges.htm" class="external text" title="http://pbsg.npolar.no/Meetings/PressReleases/02-Morges.htm" rel="nofollow">Proceedings of the 2nd Working Meeting of Polar Bear Specialists</a>" (HTML) in <a href="http://pbsg.npolar.no/" class="external text" title="http://pbsg.npolar.no/" rel="nofollow"><i>Polar Bears</i></a>., Morges, Switzerland: <a href="/wiki/IUCN" title="IUCN" class="mw-redirect">IUCN</a>. <span class="reference-accessdate">Retrieved on <span class="mw-formatted-date" title="2007-10-24"><a href="/wiki/2007" title="2007">2007</a>-<a href="/wiki/October_24" title="October 24">10-24</a></span></span>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=proceeding&amp;rft.btitle=&amp;rft.atitle=Proceedings+of+the+2nd+Working+Meeting+of+Polar+Bear+Specialists&amp;rft.date=1970&amp;rft.pub=%5B%5BIUCN%5D%5D&amp;rft.place=Morges%2C+Switzerland&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fpbsg.npolar.no%2FMeetings%2FPressReleases%2F02-Morges.htm"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li id="cite_note-81"><b><a href="#cite_ref-81" title="">^</a></b> Norway passed a series of increasingly strict regulations from 1965 to 1973, and has completely banned hunting since then. The Soviet Union banned all hunting in 1956. Canada began imposing hunting quotas in 1968. The U.S. began regulating in 1971 and adopted the <a href="/wiki/Marine_Mammal_Protection_Act" title="Marine Mammal Protection Act">Marine Mammal Protection Act</a> in 1972.</li>
