<li id="cite_note-114"><b><a href="#cite_ref-114" title="">^</a></b> Bruemmer, p. 101. In an meeting of the five circumpolar nations on <span class="mw-formatted-date" title="1965-09-06"><span class="mw-formatted-date" title="09-06"><a href="/wiki/September_6" title="September 6">September 6</a></span>, <a href="/wiki/1965" title="1965">1965</a></span>, estimates of the worldwide population ranged from 5,000 to 19,000. "The truth was, no one knew... Scientific research had been sketchy and knowledge of the polar bear was based largely on stories brought back by explorers and hunters."</li>
