<li id="cite_note-125"><b><a href="#cite_ref-125" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="" id="CITEREFKochnev_AA.2C_Etylin_VM.2C_Kavry_VI.2C_Siv-Siv_EB.2C_Tanko_IV2009">Kochnev AA, Etylin VM, Kavry VI, Siv-Siv EB, Tanko IV (December 17-19, 2002). <i>Ritual Rites and Customs of the Natives of Chukotka connected with the Polar Bear</i>. Preliminary report submitted for the meeting of the Alaska Nanuuq Commission (Nome, Alaska, USA). pp. p. 1-3.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Ritual+Rites+and+Customs+of+the+Natives+of+Chukotka+connected+with+the+Polar+Bear&amp;rft.aulast=Kochnev+AA%2C+Etylin+VM%2C+Kavry+VI%2C+Siv-Siv+EB%2C+Tanko+IV&amp;rft.au=Kochnev+AA%2C+Etylin+VM%2C+Kavry+VI%2C+Siv-Siv+EB%2C+Tanko+IV&amp;rft.date=December+17-19%2C+2002&amp;rft.pages=pp.+p.+1-3&amp;rft.pub=Preliminary+report+submitted+for+the+meeting+of+the+Alaska+Nanuuq+Commission+%28Nome%2C+Alaska%2C+USA%29&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Polar_bear"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
